article_text:
KOSSUTH, MS (WCBI) – Federal Aviation Authority Investigators will be looking into what caused a private plane to go down around 8 this morning.

The plane crashed on County Road 504 and came to a rest in the front yard of a home. One of the passengers on the plane was airlifted to a Memphis hospital while three others escpaed with bumps and bruises. the crash site is near the Alcorn County airport.
